docs.abstract: Longstanding complaints about the barriers women face in the economics profession are beginning to resonate within the male-dominated field.
docs.snippet: Longstanding complaints about the barriers women face in the economics profession are beginning to resonate within the male-dominated field.
docs.lead_paragraph: PHILADELPHIA — It is not difficult to find an all-male panel at the annual January mega-gathering of American economists. They are as common as PowerPoint presentations and pie charts. One such panel this year met to sleepily critique President Trump’s economic policies, but it was overshadowed by another panel, two ballrooms away, that jolted a profession that prides itself on cool rationality.

headline.main: Wielding Data, Women Force a Reckoning Over Bias in the Economics Field
